(1740, 741, '_akismet', 'a:2:{s:7:"comment";a:49:{s:14:"comment_author";s:12:"David Geiger";s:20:"comment_author_email";s:16:"dgeigerr@aol.com";s:15:"comment_content";s:760:"David Geiger\n\ndgeigerr@aol.com\n\nDeneve® LED Solar Flag Pole Light\n\nDeneve\nFirst I’d like to say that I love my solar LED light for my flag pole. I have even bought 3 additional lights as gifts for friends and family.\nI unfortunately do have an issue. Last week we were expecting high winds so I lowered my telescoping pole and as I did I was hit in the head with a falling battery. No injury thankfully. I looked up to find the one of the battery covers had fallen off. I found the cover easily but the very tiny screws have proven evasive. \nCan I please get two screws for this unit so I can continue to enjoy your product? Thank you for your efforts in this matter.\nDavid\nAD: 8052 Celestial Circle Liberty Township, Ohio 45044\nPH: 513.260.2768\n\nQBG7\n\nQBG7";s:4:"blog";s:20:"http://deneveusa.com";s:9:"blog_lang";s:5:"en_US";s:12:"blog_charset";s:5:"UTF-8";s:7:"user_ip";s:13:"72.49.196.195";s:10:"user_agent";s:71:"Mozilla/5.0 (compatible; MSIE 10.0; Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/6.0)";s:8:"referrer";s:31:"http://deneveusa.com/contact-us";s:12:"comment_type";s:12:"contact-form";s:15:"SERVER_SOFTWARE";s:6:"Apache";s:11:"REQUEST_URI";s:11:"/contact-us";s:14:"CONTENT_LENGTH";s:4:"1014";s:12:"CONTENT_TYPE";s:48:"application/x-www-form-urlencoded; charset=UTF-8";s:13:"DOCUMENT_ROOT";s:25:"/home/aychell/public_html";s:17:"GATEWAY_INTERFACE";s:7:"CGI/1.1";s:11:"HTTP_ACCEPT";s:46:"application/json, text/javascript, */*; q=0.01";s:20:"HTTP_ACCEPT_ENCODING";s:13:"gzip, deflate";s:20:"HTTP_ACCEPT_LANGUAGE";s:5:"en-US";s:18:"HTTP_CACHE_CONTROL";s:8:"no-cache";s:15:"HTTP_CONNECTION";s:10:"Keep-Alive";s:8:"HTTP_DNT";s:1:"1";s:9:"HTTP_HOST";s:13:"deneveusa.com";s:12:"HTTP_REFERER";s:31:"http://deneveusa.com/contact-us";s:15:"HTTP_USER_AGENT";s:71:"Mozilla/5.0 (compatible; MSIE 10.0; Windows NT 6.1; WOW64;