ustomer Service to place orders.\r\n\r\nPlease note: We may contract third-party service providers to help us evaluate our web site traffic and visitors’ preferences. These providers are not permitted access to customer-specific information unless it’s necessary to help us conduct business and improve our services.\r\n\r\n<b>Can I turn cookies off?</b>\r\n\r\nYou have three options when managing cookies on your computer:\r\n\r\n1. Allow cookies to be placed on your Web browser\r\n\r\n2.  Require your computer to warn you when cookies are sent\r\n\r\n3. Turn off all cookies\r\n\r\nTo review and maintain your cookie settings, access the Help menu in your Web browser (e.g. Internet Explorer, Chrome, and Firefox).\r\n\r\nPlease note: If you disable cookies, you cannot access some of the features on the Deneve web site or they may not work properly (e.g. the shopping cart).  In addition, disabling cookies could impact your overall experience while visiting the web site.\r\n\r\nIf you disable cookies, please contact Deneve Customer Care to place orders. To contact us, click <b>Contact Us</b> in the menu along the top of your page.\r\n\r\n<b>Do we disclose your information to outside parties?</b>\r\n\r\nWe do not sell, trade, or transfer specific customer information to outside parties without providing you advanced notice. The term, "outside parties," does not include the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Our hosting partners and other third parties who assist us in operating our web site, conducting business, or serving customers.  They are provided only appropriate information and are contractually obligated to maintain confidentiality as outlined above.</li>\r\n	<li>We may also release customer information as appropriate to comply with the law, enforce our web site policies, or protect our or others'' rights, property, or safety.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nInformation that is not customer-specific as well as aggregated data that is outside the scope of this Privacy Policy and may be provided to other parties for marketing, advertising, or other purposes.\r\n\r\n<b>How do you maintain your personal information and change your communication preferences?</b>\r\n\r\nTo update your personal information log into your Deneve account.  If you need assistance, please contact Deneve Customer Service. To contact us, click <b>Contact Us</b> in the menu along the top of your page.\r\n\r\nTo opt-out or update your e-mail address and communications preferences, log into your Deneve account and access your email settings.\r\n\r\nPotential delay: Although we receive your updates immediately, there may be email correspondence already in our production queue.  As a result, it is possible that you may receive email after you opt-out of our marketing communications program due to our production schedule.\r\n\r\nTo remove your information from our database log into your Deneve account, then delete your shipping and billing addresses as well as your payment information.\r\n\r\nPlease note that we may retain information regarding specific sales transactions to complete orders and maintain our accounting records.\r\n\r\n<b>Scope of our Privacy Policy</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Links to other web sites:  </b>To increase the value of the Deneve web site, we may provide links on our web site to other sites to provide information that you may find of interest or to enhance the overall functionality of our web site and improve your shopping experiences. These third parties operate independently from Deneve and maintain their own policies regarding privacy and security. Therefore, we have no responsibility or liability for the content or the activities of these web sites.  We recommend that you review the policies of those sites that you visit.  To maintain the integrity of our own web site, we welcome your feedback about these links, especially if a link does not function properly.\r\n\r\n<b>On-line information:  </b>The Privacy Policy outlined above applies only to the information collected via our web site; it does not pertain to information collected through other sources.\r\n\r\n<b>Terms and Conditions: </b>For additional information regarding the use of our web site as well as disclaimers and limitations, please visit our <b>Terms and Conditions</b> section.\r\n\r\n<b>Your consent: </b>By using our web site, you consent to the above Privacy Policy.\r\n\r\n<b>Updates to our Privacy Policy: </b>Updates to our Privacy Policy will be posted on this web page. Policy changes will apply only to information collected after the date of the change. This policy was last modified on November 9, 2013.\r\n\r\n<b>Customer service is paramount </b>\r\n\r\nThank you for your interest in Deneve. We value your feedback and would be happy to answer any questions.  To contact us, click <b>Customer Service</b> in the menu along the bottom of your page.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Privacy Policy', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '735-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-06 23:18:54', '2013-11-06 23:18:54', '', 735, 'http://deneveusa.com/archives/737', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
