(885, 1, '2014-04-07 23:05:12', '2014-04-07 23:05:12', '<h2><strong>HISTORY</strong></h2>\r\nDeneve''s humble roots trace back to its founding by a family in 2013 out of a garage in Southern California.  Someone asked, "Hey, why don''t we try selling our products on the Internet?"  Somebody else responded, "I''ve been hearing about the Internet lately!  Sounds like a great idea!"  This happened in early 2013.  We''ll admit we''re about 15 years late.  Sorry to keep you waiting for so long.\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong>WHO ARE WE?</strong></h2>\r\nWe''re a family! -- and that''s all we''ll say for now.  The web is a scary enough place that we prefer not disclosing anything beyond this.  We hope you understand.\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, we''re not unreachable!  There a few convenient ways for you to reach us.  Unlike some of our competitors, we don''t have obscure email addresses or funny foreign-looking phone numbers to rack up your phone charges.  It''s easy to have a dialogue with us.  You can either use the <a title="Contact Us" href="http://deneveusa.com/wp/contact-us">contact form</a>, or contact us via one of the following methods:\r\n<h4>Mail:</h4>\r\n340 E. First St. #335\r\nTustin, CA 92781\r\n\r\n<h4>Email:</h4>\r\ncontact@deneveusa.com\r\n<h2><strong>MISSION\r\n</strong></h2>\r\nWe have a straightforward policy for selecting or designing our products: if it''s good enough for us, then it better be good enough for you!  Maybe we should tone down our corporate arrogance a little bit.  Hrmm...\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong>SOCIAL RESPONSIBILITY</strong></h2>\r\nAt Deneve, the "triple bottom line" is alive and well, as we seek to do right, do well and do good in support of people, profits and the planet.  This means we''re striving to play an active role in the communities in which we operate.\r\n\r\nDeneve''s founders have a long, personal history of donating and providing charitably.  Even as hectic as running Deneve can be, we strongly believe that, at minimum, we help you pay things forward by making charitable contributions.  We strive to donate a portion of a product''s net proceeds to a charitable organization who is relevant to the product, as often as once every 3 months.  So that your money will work most effectively, we scrutinize the recipients of our donations by analyzing their overhead &amp; efficiency on trustworthy watchdog resources such as <a title="http://www.charitywatch.org" href="http://www.charitywatch.org/" target="_blank">charitywatch.org</a> and <a title="http://www.charitynavigator.org" href="http://www.charitynavigator.org" target="_blank">charitynavigator.org</a>.  We urge you to do the same when considering your own personal donations.\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>NATURAL STEWARDS</strong></h2>\r\nBecause we believe in being outstanding stewards of our beautiful nation, Deneve''s US-based operations abides by a 100% zero-landfill policy.  All leftover materials are recycled, including electronics.  Deneve keeps e-waste at a minimum by repurposing or reselling most of our electronics.  In the even we have leftover e-waste, we deliver our electronic scrap to local state approved e-recycling facilities participating in the CalRecycle Covered Electronic Waste System which have in-house machinery to pulverize electronics into raw, reusable materials.  This ensure electronics are not shipped to external non-audited facilities which employ child labor, which may be exposed to toxins while manually sorting and processing e-waste.  Also, Deneve strives to be a paperless organization.  90%+ of our processes and operations are paperless.', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '560-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-07 23:05:12', '2014-04-07 23:05:12', '', 560, 'http://deneveusa.com/archives/885', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
