(577, 1, '2013-07-03 07:10:13', '2013-07-03 07:10:13', '<strong>HISTORY</strong>\r\n\r\nDeneve''s humble roots trace back to its founding by a family in 2013 out of a garage in Southern California.  We have a straightforward policy for selecting or designing our products: if it''s good enough for us, it''s good enough to try selling to see if it''s good enough for you!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>WHO ARE WE?</strong>\r\n\r\nWe''re a family! -- and that''s all we''ll say for now.  The web is a scary enough place that we prefer not disclosing anything beyond this.  We hope you understand.\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, we''re not unreachable!  There''s a few ways for you to reach us.  Unlike some of our competitors, we don''t have obscure email addresses or funny foreign-looking phone numbers to rack up your phone charges.  We make it convenient for you to have a dialogue with us.  You can either use the <a title="Contact Us" href="http://deneveusa.com/wp/contact-us">contact form</a>, or contact us via one of the following methods:\r\n<h4>Mail:</h4>\r\nDeneve\r\n\r\n340 E First St. #335\r\n\r\nTustin, CA 92781\r\n<h4>Phone / Fax:</h4>\r\n949-391-2999\r\n<h4>Email:</h4>\r\ncontactus@deneveusa.com\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>SOCIAL RESPONSIBILITY</strong>\r\n\r\nAt Deneve, the "triple bottom line" is alive and well, as we seek to do right, do well and do good in support of people, profits and the planet.  that means we''re striving to play an active role in the communities in which we operate.\r\n\r\nEven as hectic as running Deneve can be, we strongly believe that, at minimum, we help you pay things forward by making charitable contributions.  We strive to donate a portion of a product''s net proceeds to a charitable organization who is relevant to the product, as often as once every 3 months.  So that your money will work most effectively, we scrutinize the recipients of our donations by analyzing their overhead &amp; efficiency on trustworthy watchdog resources such as <a title="http://www.charitywatch.org" href="http://www.charitywatch.org/" target="_blank">charitywatch.org</a> and <a title="charitynavigator.org" href="charitynavigator.org" target="_blank">charitynavigator.org</a>.  We urge you to do the same when considering your own personal donations.\r\n\r\nDeneve''s founders have a long, personal history of donating and providing charitably.  One of our founders is fond of a story to demonstrate how interrelated we all are as human beings. More than 10 years ago, he had reported fraudulent activity occurring on his Ebay account, but not hoping much in the form of a response, since the amount defrauded wasn''t high, and law enforcement officials usually have much larger fish to fry.  Well, in this instance, one detective from Houma, LA, not only took up the case with vigorous enthusiasm, he actually followed the case and the perpetrator all the way to Chicago where the suspect was finally caught.  And throughout the months-long ordeal, he repeatedly touched base with this co-founder to update the co-founder (with much enthusiasm in his voice over the phone) on the progress of the case.  Needless to say, the co-founder was pleasantly surprised by all of this.  Lastly, but not least, the detective even managed to recover some of the damages, and cut the co-founder a check accordingly.  Again, we''re probably talking about no more than $50.  It''s been at least 10+ years, and the co-founder doesn''t recall the exact amount anymore.\r\n\r\nFast forward to August 2005.  Many of us may not recall precisely what happened that month, but we''re confident that one word will help joggle your memory: Katrina.  Hurricane Katrina ravages and devastates the Gulf States.  The co-founder distinctly remembers trying to come to his senses while being stunned by image after image, video after video, of the horrific visual horror, the tragedy that uprooted and obliterated so many lives on his TV in his apartment that he was sharing with a buddy of his in Los Angeles.  A few hours after Katrina hit Louisiana, this co-founder was glued to the set, watching the news as he had been, when suddenly a chill ran up his spine when the news started mentioning one city, a city he''d never visited or been in, but yet, it was a city from his past: Houma, LA.\r\n\r\nIt was as if the co-founder''s Pavlovian instincts had kicked in, like a bell was furiously ringing in his head.\r\n\r\nWithout much hesitation, this co-founder frantically searched for the name of the eager Lieutenant who''d helped him a few years earlier, found the address for the Houma PD, and cut a check in the amount that was several times that which he''d received from Houma.\r\n\r\nThis co-founder hopes that somehow the check reached Houma, that somehow the funds helped the Lieutenant out, and that it made some impact, however small and insignificant it may be.\r\n\r\nTo this day, the co-founder has never met the Lieutenant in person.  But through this experiencing, the founder understood the intrinsic connection and responsibility that we all have with one another.  We are one human race.  We should strive to make it our calling to try helping and making a positive impact on each other, somehow.', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '560-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-07-03 07:10:13', '2013-07-03 07:10:13', '', 560, 'http://deneveusa.com/wp/archives/577', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
