contributions.  We strive to donate a portion of a product''s net proceeds to a charitable organization who is relevant to the product, as often as once every 3 months.  So that your money will work most effectively, we scrutinize the recipients of our donations by analyzing their overhead &amp; efficiency on trustworthy watchdog resources such as <a title="http://www.charitywatch.org" href="http://www.charitywatch.org/" target="_blank">charitywatch.org</a> and <a title="http://www.charitynavigator.org" href="http://www.charitynavigator.org" target="_blank">charitynavigator.org</a>.  We urge you to do the same when considering your own personal donations.\n\n<h2><strong>NATURAL STEWARDS</strong></h2>\nBecause we believe in being outstanding stewards of our beautiful nation, Deneve''s US-based operations abides by a 100% zero-landfill policy.  All leftover materials are recycled, including electronics.  Deneve keeps e-waste at a minimum by repurposing or reselling most of our electronics.  In the eWe deliver our electronic scrap to local state approved e-recycling facilities participating in the CalRecycle Covered Electronic Waste System which have in-house machinery to pulverize electronics into raw, reusable materials.  This ensure electronics are not shipped to external facilities which employ child labor which may be exposed to toxins while manually sorting and processing e-waste.  Also, Deneve strives to be a paperless organization.  90%+ of our processes and operations are paperless.', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '560-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-04-07 23:04:36', '2014-04-07 23:04:36', '', 560, 'http://deneveusa.com/wp/archives/566', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
